Logic-1 : love6


The number 6 is a truly great number. 
Given two int values, a and b, return true if either one is 6. Or if their sum or difference is 6. Note: the function Math.abs(num) computes the absolute value of a number.


love6(6, 4) → true
love6(4, 5) → false
love6(1, 5) → true

public boolean love6(int a, int b) {
    if (a == 6 || b == 6) {
            return true;
        }
        int sum1 = a + b;
        int sum2 = Math.abs(a - b);
        return sum1 == 6 || sum2 == 6;
}
